!begin_node (!kw [no_toc_subsubnodes])
!html_name cmd_no_toc_subsubnodes

Do not output seubsections in tables of contents.

!begin_xlist [(!TYPEPOSITION)]

!item [(!TYPEPOSITION)] (!SWITCH), (!PREAMBLE)

!item [(!SYNTAX)] (!T)!/no_toc_subsubnodes [(!FORMAT)<](!t)

!item [(!DESCRIPTION)]
If you use this switch inside the preamble UDO will print only the
chapter titles and section titles inside the table of contents.

Another possibily is to use the switch (!KW [depth]) with
the (!KW [toc]) command.

!item [(!EXAMPLE)]
(!T)!/no_toc_subsubnodes [win,stg,html](!t)

!item [(!EXISTSSINCE)] Release~5 Patchlevel~8

!item [(!SEEALSO)]
(!KW [tableofcontents]), (!KW [toc]), (!KW [depth]), (!link [Tables of contents] [Tables of contents])

!end_xlist

!end_node
